summary: This document appears to be preparation notes for an Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA) or detective regarding upcoming testimony. It references a witness who reviewed CDs containing photos (but no videos) and a chart (GX 1101), and notes that some photos had initials 'GM' or '0' underneath them, possibly indicating the photographer.

events.title: Preparation for testimony
events.description: An AUSA or detective prepares for testimony, noting a witness's review of CDs containing photos (no videos) and verification of chart GX 1101's accuracy.

keyFacts: A witness reviewed CDs that contained only photos, no videos.
The witness confirmed the accuracy of chart GX 1101.
Some photos in binders had initials 'GM' or '0' underneath, which appeared to indicate who took the photos.
The document is subject to a protective order covering specific paragraphs (7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
The document is part of preparation for testimony, likely in a legal proceeding related to the Epstein case.
